1. A Boolean value is either true or false. E.g. 4 == (2+2), 4 == (2+3), 1 > 0
2. A flowchart is a chart that shows how computers logically evaluate our code.
                                                 |
                                                 |
                                                 |
                                                 |
                                              Condition
                                                 |
                     name = "Dinh Quy" ======== else   ======== name = "Minh Duc"
                            |                    |                    |
                            |                    |                     |
                      print(“Hand some")         |           even_more_handsome = True
                       webbrowser.open(“https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=04854XqcfCY”)
3. Nested conditionals are cases when an if/else statement contains another if/else statement inside them. E.g.

n = int(input("Ban bao nhieu tuoi"))
if n < 12:
    print("Ban dang hoc cap 1")
else
    if n >=12 and n <16:
        print("Ban dang hoc cap 2")
    else
        print("Ban dang hoc cap 3 tro len")